body:
@yuliskov 

I now tried 2160p60 playback on a BRAVIA ATV2 (MediaTek MT5891 @ 1GHz) with STubeNext 10.54 with the updated ExoPlayer 2.12.1. Looks much better now, similar to the original YouTube app. There is some minor micro-stuttering every few seconds left.

I wonder which [MediaCodec mode](https://medium.com/google-exoplayer/improved-rendering-performance-operating-mediacodec-in-asynchronous-mode-and-asynchronous-buffer-3026207850b2) ExoPlayer operates in. I don't see one being explicitly set by STubeNext. So I assume it operates in `OPERATION_MODE_SYNCHRONOUS`? How about [Tunneled playback mode](https://medium.com/google-exoplayer/tunneled-video-playback-in-exoplayer-84f084a8094d)?

